column6: Damien Chazelle should get it, but the Academy might split Best Picture from Best Director in order to spread the wealth
Same aggregate wisdom of the crowd method as most of my pervious Oscars predictions. Hacksaw Ridge director at 0% after not even receiving a Screen Actor's Guild nomination.
A musical about how tough it is to be handsome in Hollywood. It's clickbait for Oscar votes.
La La Land is best picture, so Chazelle should edge out Jenkins. Others are on a second tier.
